    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>diced shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped parsley</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> – this is your <strong>chimichurri</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle & mortar? Pulse in a food processor!</p><p>Combine the <strong>courgette ribbons</strong> and the <strong>chimichurri</strong> in a large bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> chimichurri courgette</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
