    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>lettuce </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper, then remove 1 <strong>leaf </strong>per person and set aside</p><p>Chop the <strong>inner core </strong>into quarters, lengthways</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> (not a fan of raw garlic? Just add a little!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a small splash of<strong> water </strong>– this is your<strong> garlic sauce</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>halloumi</strong> in half, lengthways (like you're slicing a burger bun!)</p>",
